article.headline: Belmont 83, Kennesaw 64
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Boomer Herndon scored 21 points that led five in double-figures, and Belmont downed Kennesaw State 86-64 Friday night for the Bruins' eighth victory in nine games. Belmont (16-10, 14-5 Atlantic Sun) trailed by as much as much as eight points in the second half, but Andy Wicke hit a 3-pointer with 13:30 left that put the Bruins ahead to stay. Belmont finished the game with a 20-6 run. Kennesaw State (12-16, 10-9) lost its fourth straight. Belmont outrebounded the Owls 29-24 and had a decided advantage at the free throw line, 17-of-22 compared to 5-of-8. Wicke finished with 17 points for Belmont, Josh Goodwin 16 points, Justin Hare had 14 and Brian Collins 10. Ronell Wooten led Kennesaw State with 17 points. Golden Ingle had 12, Andre Morgan 11 and Brent Ragsdale and Dusty Moore each had 10.
